Facebook has selected 60 finalists from the hundreds of entries it received from across the Middle East and Africa for the Bots for Messenger Developer Challenge. 
The Bots for Messenger Challenge is a contest to recognise and reward developers who create the most innovative new bots on Messenger.

The categories: 
#Gaming 
#entertainment; 
#productivity
#utility; and 
#social good.

The 60 finalist teams (10 per category in Middle East/North Africa and sub-Saharan Africa) each won a Gear VR and mobile phone, one hour of Facebook mentorship, and tools and services from FbStart (Developers.Facebook.com/fbstart), a Facebook program designed to help early stage mobile start-ups build and grow their bots. All student teams who made it to the finals won an additional $2,000.

Facebook will contact the finalists and connect them with a mentor. They will need to resubmit their bots before midnight (GMT) on June 2 to qualify to win.

“And he said, 'Abba, Father, all things are possible for you. Remove this cup from me. Yet not what I will, but what you will.'” (Mark‬ ‭14:36‬ ‭ESV‬‬)
**
This passage describes what happened in the moments before Jesus was seized and sent to be crucified - the darkest hour of His earthly life. And in that moment, Jesus set the ultimate example of how we should live out faith in our lives. He concluded His prayer by dying to His own will and submitting to the will of His Father, knowing it was best. Our heavenly Father's will for us is always best - no matter the situation or circumstance, no matter how well-equipped or ill-equipped we are for the task. There are many things He calls us to according to His will that we will never understand this side of heaven. We have to accept that and stop questioning God and asking why because we cannot even begin to fathom His reasonings and plan (Isaiah 55:8-9). I have been studying the #ArmorofGodStudy by @priscillashirer and this week we looked in-depth at the shield of faith. <"If you are struggling to move forward in obedience to God, you do not need bigger faith. You just need to realize how big your God is. The more faithful and strong you believe him to be, the more willing you will be to depend on him. Your level of faith will always be tied to your perception of God."> Knowing God on an intimate level is key. Once we truly know our God it then becomes easy to trust Him. We need to strengthen our faith in who God is. Our faith is strengthened when we read the Bible and see from beginning to end the mercy and love of our God that spans across generations. Our faith is strengthened when we look back over our own lives and reflect on how God has been so good to us and has worked even the bad things together for our good and His glory (Romans 8:28). Our faith is strengthened when we dwell on His character through worship and prayer. This is a daily battle to die to our will and submit to God's will. So let's strengthen our faith today and spend time in God's holy presence. You'll be amazed at how quickly you begin to trust Him and rely on Him more each day. #submit #thywillbedone #trust #seekgod #knowgod #trustingod
